     Plan: Refactor Extent Manager to Dynamic Slab-Based Allocation

     Context

     The extent manager currently requires callers to pre-specify all size
     classes and slot counts at initialize time. This is inflexible ‚ÄĒ callers
     must know their workload up front. The refactor changes initialization to
     accept a total device size and slab size, then dynamically carves slabs
     from that space as new size classes are demanded via create_extent. Each
     slab serves one size class; multiple slabs can serve the same class
     (auto-grow when full).

     Interface Change

     File: components/interfaces/src/iblock_device.rs (line 459)

     // Before:
     fn initialize(&self, sizes: Vec<u32>, slots: Vec<u32>, ns_id: u32) ->
     Result<(), NvmeBlockError>;
     // After:
     fn initialize(&self, total_size_bytes: u64, slab_size_bytes: u32, ns_id:
     u32) -> Result<(), NvmeBlockError>;

     open, set_dma_alloc, and all IExtentManager methods are unchanged.

