     ‚Ēė

     Max 256 slabs inline (40 + 256√ó12 = 3112, fits in 4096-byte block).

     Slab Internal Layout

     Each slab is slab_size_blocks contiguous LBAs:
     [bitmap_blocks][record_blocks].
     - num_slots = slab_size_blocks - ceil(num_slots / 32768) ‚ÄĒ solved
     iteratively
     - For 1 GiB slab (262144 blocks): 262136 slots, 8 bitmap blocks
     - Minimum slab: 2 blocks (1 bitmap + 1 slot)

     State Model

     File: src/state.rs ‚ÄĒ full rewrite

     struct SlabDescriptor {
         slab_index: usize, size_class: u32, start_lba: u64,
         bitmap_start_lba: u64, record_start_lba: u64,
         bitmap_blocks: u32, num_slots: u32, bitmap: AllocationBitmap,
     }
     struct ExtentManagerState {
         index: HashMap<u64, ExtentMetadata>,
         slabs: Vec<SlabDescriptor>,
         size_class_slabs: HashMap<u32, Vec<usize>>,  // size_class ‚Üí slab 
     indices
         total_blocks: u64, slab_size_blocks: u32,
         next_free_lba: u64, namespace_id: u32,
     }

     Key methods: find_free_slot(size_class), can_allocate_slab(),
     add_slab_descriptor().

     Metadata Change

     File: src/metadata.rs ‚ÄĒ add pub slab_index: usize to ExtentMetadata
     (in-memory only, not serialized to disk). Enables O(1) slab lookup in
     remove_extent.

     create_extent Flow

     1. Write-lock state, check duplicate key, validate size_class (128KiB-5MiB,
      4KiB-aligned)
     2. find_free_slot(size_class) ‚ÄĒ scan slabs for this class with a free bit
     3. If none: allocate_slab(size_class):
     a. Check space (next_free_lba + slab_size_blocks <= total_blocks) and slab
     count (< 256)
     b. Zero all slab blocks (crash-safe pre-commit)
     c. Write initial bitmap blocks
     d. Write updated superblock with new slab entry (atomic commit point)
     e. Add SlabDescriptor to state
     4. Two-phase write: record block, then bitmap block (same crash semantics
     as current)
     5. Insert into index

     Recovery

     File: src/recovery.rs ‚ÄĒ signature changes to recover(client, slabs: &mut 
     Vec<SlabDescriptor>, ns_id). Per-slot logic (the bitmap/record cross-check
     match block) is preserved verbatim. Outer loop iterates slabs instead of
     size_configs.

