     11. benches/*.rs ‚ÄĒ update initialize calls

     Key Design Decisions

     - New magic, not version bump: V2 magic ensures clean rejection of V1
     superblocks and vice versa
     - No pre-allocated slabs at format time: initialize writes only the
     superblock (1 block). First create_extent triggers slab allocation
     - Zero slab blocks before superblock commit: If crash occurs during
     zeroing, superblock still points to old next_free_lba ‚ÄĒ partially written
     region is invisible to recovery
     - Write lock covers slab allocation: Slab allocation is rare and amortized;
      no need for a separate lock
     - slab_index in ExtentMetadata: O(1) slab lookup in remove_extent without
     scanning

