‚óŹ Now I need to rewrite all test files. The key changes:
  1. initialize() now takes (total_size_bytes: u64, slab_size_bytes: u32, ns_id:
   u32)
  2. No more pre-specified size classes and slots
  3. Size classes are determined at create_extent time ‚ÄĒ slabs are dynamically
  allocated
  4. Need enough total space for the slabs that will be allocated

  Let me think about the sizes. A 1 GiB slab has 262144 blocks. For tests we
  want smaller slabs. Let's use small slabs to keep tests fast. A slab of 128
  blocks (512 KiB) would give ~127 slots ‚ÄĒ good for most tests. For the
  out-of-space test, we need very tight space.

